.TH "WEBGL2RENDERINGCONTEXT.TEXSUBIMAGE3D" "3JS" "August 27, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
WebGL2RenderingContext.texSubImage3D \- WebGL2RenderingContext:
texSubImage3D() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]texSubImage3D()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]WebGL2RenderingContext\f[R] interface of the WebGL API specifies a
three\-dimensional sub\-rectangle for a texture image.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
texSubImage3D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, width, height, depth, format, type, srcData)
texSubImage3D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, width, height, depth, format, type, srcData, srcOffset)
texSubImage3D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, width, height, depth, format, type, source)
texSubImage3D(target, level, xoffset, yoffset, zoffset, width, height, depth, format, type, offset)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]target\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the binding point (target) of the active
texture.
Possible values:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_3D\f[R]: A three\-dimensional texture.
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]gl.TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY\f[R]: A two\-dimensional array texture.
.RE
.TP
\f[B]level\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the level of detail.
Level 0 is the base image level and level \f[I]n\f[R] is the n\-th
mipmap reduction level.
.TP
\f[B]xoffset\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the x offset within the texture image.
.TP
\f[B]yoffset\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the y offset within the texture image.
.TP
\f[B]zoffset\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLint\f[R] specifying the z offset within the texture image.
.TP
\f[B]width\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the width of the texture in texels.
.TP
\f[B]height\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the height of the texture in texels.
.TP
\f[B]depth\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLsizei\f[R] specifying the depth of the texture/the number of
textures in a \f[CR]TEXTURE_2D_ARRAY\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]format\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying how each integer element in the raw texel
data should be interpreted as color components.
.TP
\f[B]type\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLenum\f[R] specifying the size of each integer element in the
raw texel data.
For the combinations of \f[CR]format\f[R] and \f[CR]type\f[R] available,
see \f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.texSubImage2D()\f[R].
.PP
The texture source can be provided in one of three ways: from an
\f[CR]ArrayBuffer\f[R] (possibly shared) using \f[CR]srcData\f[R] and
\f[CR]srcOffset\f[R]; from a DOM pixel \f[CR]source\f[R]; or from
\f[CR]gl.PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER\f[R] using \f[CR]offset\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]srcData\f[R]
A \f[CR]TypedArray\f[R] or \f[CR]DataView\f[R] containing the compressed
texture data.
Its type must match the \f[CR]type\f[R] parameter; see
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext.texImage2D()\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]srcOffset\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An integer specifying the index of \f[CR]srcData\f[R] to start reading
from.
Defaults to \f[CR]0\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]source\f[R]
Read from a DOM pixel source, which can be one of:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]ImageBitmap\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]ImageData\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLImageElement\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLCanvasElement\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]HTMLVideoElement\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]OffscreenCanvas\f[R]
.IP \(bu 2
\f[CR]VideoFrame\f[R]
.RE
.TP
\f[B]offset\f[R]
A \f[CR]GLintptr\f[R] specifying the starting address in the buffer
bound to \f[CR]gl.PIXEL_UNPACK_BUFFER\f[R].
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
gl.texSubImage3D(
  gl.TEXTURE_3D,
  0,
  0,
  0,
  0,
  image.width,
  image.height,
  1,
  gl.RGBA,
  gl.UNSIGNED_BYTE,
  image,
);
.EE
